<p style="margin:0 0 22px;font-size:18px;line-height:1.6;color:#1a1a1a">Most pain creams <strong>only work on the surface</strong>. The menthol or camphor makes your skin feel cold or hot, and that's all it is, a sensation that fades in about twenty minutes.</p>
<p style="margin:0 0 22px;font-size:18px;line-height:1.6;color:#1a1a1a">But the ache isn't on the surface. <strong>It's deeper</strong>, in the joint, the knuckle, the spot that everything you've ever rubbed in could never reach.</p>
<p style="margin:0 0 22px;font-size:18px;line-height:1.6;color:#1a1a1a">And it was never your joints being too far gone. An ordinary cream's molecules are simply too big to pass through your skin, so they sit on top and do nothing. <strong>Picture trying to push a tennis ball through a keyhole.</strong></p>
<p style="margin:0;font-size:18px;line-height:1.6;color:#1a1a1a"><strong>Nanoization shrinks those molecules</strong> down small enough to slip right through, so NanoXtreme <strong>absorbs up to 10 times more</strong>, all the way down to the joint that's been keeping you stiff.</p>
